{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"50cd70fb-0071-4f96-a87e-b26538ee849a","content":"Here's the summary:\n\n- **`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is no longer needed.** In .NET 9 it was required to opt `dotnet test` into MTP mode. In .NET 10, MTP is the default — the property is a no-op.\n- **Keep `EnableMSTestRunner`** — this tells MSTest to produce a self-contained test executable using MTP (required).\n- **`dotnet test` just works** — it will discover and run your MTP-based test app natively without VSTest at all.\n\nYour updated project file:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n</Project>\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3895b55e-8fe2-4a7a-b4ba-3c7c3634aa32","outputTokens":255,"requestId":"A02B:3C520:C5A926:E6D527:69FE8732"},"id":"a5b35000-79cd-4513-aa62-dbb21a2f284d","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:00:39.626Z","parentId":"e45ec771-e161-4b13-a33a-8a58bd13b1ad"}
